column5: Ok guys this is my first pic upload to the site. (from BB playbook). Hope it works.  I was out to the local fishn hole a few days ago and pulled this little guy out. Is it just me , kinda looks like a rock bass crappie cross. John Http://i1153.photobucket.com/albums/p507/skidoosafari/th_IMG-20120425-00123.jpg
That's one small picture.. but it sure looks like Ontario's finest game fish to me! A rock bass...
Oops guess I should have resized.  Have to work on that.
Just a rock bass...I mean WOW sweet rock bass!!!
Yep a rock bass (that is crappie to catch). We get them pretty big here in a few local lakes and they can get really dark mid summer.
Yes we get some monsters up at my camp. ( suburbs of barrys bay! ) lol
I didn't realize how big it was when I caught it , last year in AP I caught a rock bass that must of been about 2.5 pounds, pretty close to an ontario record
That's a rock bass ... not a cross ...

A buddy of mine got one that was at least 2 pounds maybe more last summer, i wish i would weighed it now lol  they get pretty big if theres not many other fish to compete with for food, there very aggressive and will eat almost anything
All fishermen are liars, except you and me.....and I have my doubts about you.....
